// Google Docs sharing permission levels:

// RESTRICTED
// - Only specific people you add can access
// - Best for: confidential client documents, financial records
// - Example: the client's contract draft

// ANYONE WITH THE LINK — Viewer
// - Anyone who has the link can read but not edit
// - Best for: published reports, reference documents
// - Example: a completed project brief sent to stakeholders

// ANYONE WITH THE LINK — Commenter
// - Anyone with the link can add comments but not edit text
// - Best for: document reviews where you want feedback without edits
// - Example: sharing a draft proposal for stakeholder feedback

// ANYONE WITH THE LINK — Editor
// - Anyone with the link can edit the document
// - ⚠️  RISK: if this link is shared publicly or forwarded,
//    anyone on the internet can edit your document
// - Only use for: trusted internal team documents

